==Korean==

{{wikipediapar|Jjigae}}

===Etymology===

A native Korean word.  Possibly from [[찌다]] (''jjida'', "to steam") + [[개]] (''gae'', suffix denoting something small associated with an action).  Compare [[노리개]], [[지우개]].

===Noun===

'''찌개''' (jji.gae)

{{korrom|rr=jjigae|mr=tchigae|yr=ccikay}}

# A Korean dish similar to a [[stew]], typically consisting of vegetables and meat or seafood boiled in water seasoned with [[soy sauce]] and [[w:gochujang|gochujang]] or [[w:doenjang|doenjang]].

